MessageFactoryReader

public MessageFactoryReader(String resourceName,
                            ResourceBundle defaultResourceBundle,
                            Locale locale,
                            ResourceBundle.Control rbControl)
                     throws IOException
Creates a new MessageFactoryReader.

Parameters:
resourceName - the name of a resource to be loaded via the ClassLoader.getResource(String) method; must not be null
defaultResourceBundle - a ResourceBundle to use to resolve relative keys; may be null
locale - a Locale to use when loading ResourceBundles; if null then Locale.getDefault() will be used instead
rbControl - a ResourceBundle.Control to use when loading ResourceBundles; if null then Control.getControl(Control.FORMAT_DEFAULT) will be used instead
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if resourceName is null or identifies a resource that could not be opened
IOException - if an input or output error occurs

Creates a new MessageFactoryReader.

Parameters:
reader - the Reader to read from; must not be null
defaultResourceBundle - the ResourceBundle to use to resolve unqualified keys against; may be null
locale - the Locale to use for localization when loading new ResourceBundles; if null then the default Locale will be used instead
rbControl - the ResourceBundle.Control to use when loading new ResourceBundles; if null then Control.getControl(Control.FORMAT_DEFAULT) will be used instead
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if reader is null

read

public <T> MessageFactory<T> read()
                       throws IOException,
                              ParseException
Reads from this MessageFactoryReader's affiliated Reader and builds a MessageFactoryReader from the results.

To avoid resource leaks, this MessageFactoryReader should be closed after this method completes normally. This method does not call the close() method itself.

Type Parameters:
T - the type of objects new MessageFactory instances produced from this method will work with
Returns:
a new MessageFactory; never null
Throws:
IOException - if an input or output error occurs
IllegalStateException - if parsing could not be completed
ParseException - if the source code could not be parsed

close

public void close()
           throws IOException
Closes this MessageFactoryReader so that it cannot be used again. Once this method has been called, then the read() method will throw an IOException whenever it is invoked.

Specified by:
close in interface Closeable
Throws:
IOException - if an error was encountered during closing
